<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE50FFEEFF3FF0B2FC334FBB" pageId="14" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE50FFEEFF3FF0B2FEDD4F5A" blockId="14.[189,335,749,775]" box="[189,335,749,775]" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE50FFEEFF3FF0B2FEDD4F5A" bold="true" box="[189,335,749,775]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE50FFEEFF3FF0B2FEDD4F5A" bold="true" box="[189,335,749,775]" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE50FFEEFF3FF143FC334FBB" blockId="14.[189,1400,796,998]" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">
Colony encrusting, unilaminar. Autozooecia vase shaped or subhexagonal, arranged quincuncially (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE50FFEEFF44F160FEB84F04" box="[198,298,831,857]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1420,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-182@14.[189,1398,1420,1877]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Micropora vredenburgi Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0516). A. General view of the colony showing subhexagonal autozooid. B. Close-up of an autozooids showing orifices opesia, opesiules, thick mural rims and ooecia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580802/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Cryptocyst extensive, flat, surface coarsely granular and with fine pseudopores, slightly bulging in middle, sinking distally and near opesiules, bordered by thick, raised mural rim. Opesiules small, slit like, placed at proximolateral corners of orifice near lateral margins. Orifice semielliptical, wider than long, arched distally, proximal edge concave. Ooecia small, semi-immersed, smooth, with semicircular frontal surface (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE50FFEEFD93F193FDFC4FBB" box="[529,622,972,998]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1420,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-182@14.[189,1398,1420,1877]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Micropora vredenburgi Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005 (GIS/B 0516). A. General view of the colony showing subhexagonal autozooid. B. Close-up of an autozooids showing orifices opesia, opesiules, thick mural rims and ooecia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580802/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Avicularia not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE50FFEEFF3FF652FEAD48C1" pageId="14" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE50FFEEFF3FF652FEA2487A" blockId="14.[189,304,1037,1063]" box="[189,304,1037,1063]" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE50FFEEFF3FF652FEA2487A" bold="true" box="[189,304,1037,1063]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE50FFEEFF3FF652FEA2487A" bold="true" box="[189,304,1037,1063]" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE50FFEEFF3FF663FEAD48C1" blockId="14.[189,1401,1084,1180]" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">
All the essential characters agree with 
<taxonomicName id="4C374BF5DE50FFEEFD12F662FB65480A" authority="Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005" authorityName="Guha &amp; Gopikrishna" authorityYear="2005" box="[656,1271,1084,1111]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="14" pageNumber="30" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="vredenburgi">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE50FFEEFD12F662FC3A480B" box="[656,936,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="30">Micropora vredenburgi</emphasis>
Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2005
</taxonomicName>
. However, the interzooecial avicularia observed by Guha &amp; Gopikrishna (2005) were not noticed in the present specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
